(43, 19, 34, 66, 7, 14, 14, NULL, 'Connection of Blood Imagery', 'This connection highlights the significance of blood in both passages. In John 19:34, the blood that flows from Jesus'' side symbolizes the sacrificial nature of His death, while Revelation 7:14 emphasizes the cleansing power of that same blood, which purifies believers. Both passages underscore the theme of redemption through the blood of the Lamb.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 19, 34, 49, 5, 26, 26, 'water', 'Connection of Water Imagery', 'This connection highlights the theme of cleansing through water. In John 19:34, the blood and water that flow from Jesus'' side symbolize a new life and purification, which resonates with Ephesians 5:26''s emphasis on cleansing with water.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
